title: Five people injured in SE shooting
content:
Five juveniles have been injured say DC police officials, in an early morning shooting. The shooting happened shortly after midnight on the 4300 block of Wheeler Road SE.
Police officials say that a car drove up to the group of people, and suspects inside the car shot at the juveniles before driving away.
Three men and two women suffered gunshot wounds, said police, and were transported to a hospital with non-life threatening injuries.
